      <p class="lead">Vietnam has been the world's largest cashew exporter for over a decade, and Binh Phuoc province — the "Cashew Capital" — is the heart of that production. Greenie Vietnam sources white whole cashew kernels directly from qualified processors in this region, bringing export-ready kernels to importers, distributors, roasters, manufacturers, and private label brands worldwide.</p>

      <h2>The Alchemy of Basalt Red Earth</h2>
      <p>Binh Phuoc possesses a unique geological advantage. The deep, porous basalt red earth — remnants of ancient volcanic activity — provides an irreproducible mineral-rich foundation. This soil retains perfect moisture during tropical monsoon rains while allowing critical root aeration. It is this precise mineral signature that imparts the Sovereign cashew with its signature density and complex fatty acid structure.</p>

      <blockquote>
        <p><strong>Technical Note:</strong> Mineral-rich basalt soil contributes to 15% higher oil content compared to coastal cashew varieties, resulting in a creamier texture and richer flavor profile.</p>
      </blockquote>

      <p>Our farmers are not merely laborers; they are stewards of this land with knowledge passed through four generations. Each harvest season, they walk the same red earth their great-grandparents cultivated, selecting only the cashew apples that have reached peak ripeness.</p>

      <blockquote>
        <p>Not all cashews are created equal. The terroir of Binh Phuoc cannot be replicated — it must be protected.</p>
        <footer>— Greenie Vietnam Sourcing Principle</footer>
      </blockquote>

      <h2>The Artisan Process</h2>
      <p>From the patient rhythm of sun-drying to the precision of hand-shelling, every kernel is handled with uncompromising respect.</p>

      <!-- Float-right image with text wrapping -->
      <figure class="image-float-right">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1574184864702-315817b02790?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Artisan hand-shelling premium cashew kernels in Binh Phuoc" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption class="image-float-caption">Generational artisans hand-shell each kernel to preserve structural integrity.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>The shelling process is where true mastery reveals itself. Unlike industrial operations that rely on mechanical crushers — which fracture up to 18% of kernels — Greenie's partner artisans employ a hand-shelling technique passed through four generations. Each cashew nut is positioned at a precise angle against the blade, requiring intimate knowledge of the nut's internal architecture.</p>

      <p>A skilled artisan can shell over 8,000 nuts per day while maintaining a whole-kernel rate exceeding 92%. The alternative — mechanical shelling — would compromise both the structural integrity and the visual uniformity that premium buyers demand.</p>

