      <h3>The Process</h3>

      <h4 class="text-green-700 dark:text-green-400">I. Selective Harvesting</h4>
      <p>We harvest only when the cashew apple reaches peak ripeness, ensuring maximum kernel density and optimal flavor development.</p>

      <h4 class="text-green-700 dark:text-green-400">II. Natural Sun-Drying</h4>
      <p>Elevated bamboo racks allow airflow to reduce moisture to a stable 5%, preserving the natural enzyme system intact.</p>

      <h4 class="text-green-700 dark:text-green-400">III. Structural Grading</h4>
      <p>Each kernel is hand-peeled and sorted by weight. Only the "giants" — WW180 and WW210 — are selected for the Sovereign line.</p>

      <h2 class="text-green-800 dark:text-green-400">The Art of the Crunch</h2>
      <p>Binh Phuoc cashew begins with a buttery creaminess and finishes with an ethereal sweet note. The Sovereign's structure is dense and enduring, never crumbly — the result of exceptionally high monounsaturated fat content. Trusted by premium pastry chefs, our cashew kernels provide the structural integrity required for high-end confectionery while maintaining a distinct terroir identity.</p>

      <h2>Grades Available for Wholesale</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>W180</strong> — King of cashews. Large whole white kernels (170–180 nuts/lb), ideal for premium retail and gifting.</li>
        <li><strong>W240</strong> — Mid-size whole white kernels (220–240 nuts/lb), the most popular grade for retail and foodservice.</li>
        <li><strong>W320</strong> — Smaller whole white kernels (300–320 nuts/lb), cost-effective for snacking, ingredients, and manufacturing.</li>
      </ul>

